Paper 3 touches on interpretability in text classification but focuses on sentence-level explanation for long documents using masking techniques and unlabeled data, which is conceptually distinct from probing token-level attribution consistency across models. Paper 5 discusses bias mitigation via attention regularization, which relates tangentially to stable reasoning but does not assess cross-model attribution variability. None of the papers introduce metrics like Attribution Consistency Score (ACS) or Functional Divergence Index (FDI), nor do they decompose attributions into necessity and sufficiency in the context of model initialization variance.

Between the two ideas:
